    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think what you're talking about only applies to ``MODULARIZE=1`` which we don't (yet) do, so the current build I have seems to work with solc-js (and in remix/firefox and remix/chrome) without any solc-js change.\r\n\r\nAlso we explicitly disable asynchronous wasm compilation, etc. - we basically went out of our way to *not* have to change solc-js too much :-). But maybe at some point we could reconsider that... of course split files go against our current binary distribution setup, etc. - but I wouldn't be surprised if loading would be significantly faster, if we didn't need the base64 stuff, allowed asynchronous compilation, enabled streaming compilation, etc.",
